message.content:
We need to “roll‐up” all the profit contributions from transactions – in our data only “Sale...” transactions include a (pre‐computed) “profit” value. (Other types – “Purchase”, “Expense”, “Depreciation”, “Interest” and so on – are assumed to already be “net‐out” in a way and do not contribute an extra “profit” line.)

The idea is that if you add together the “profit” values from each Sale row you obtain the overall “final net profit” (an amount that – when “loss” and “profit” are netted – gives the business “net profit”, sometimes called operating income).
